fhlbi  home federal home loan bank of indianapolis about the federal home loan bank system  a nation of local lenders  watch the video fhlbi community and housing programs  learn more members are our shareholders  view investor relations careers  fhlbi  find your fit  shareholder symposium  discover new ways to transform your business  register now how we serve the federal home loan bank of indianapolis fhlbi is a regional wholesale bank that has been meeting the liquidity needs of member financial institutions throughout indiana and michigan since  our core mission is to provide a reliable source of liquidity to member banks credit unions community development financial institutions and insurance companies to support housing finance assetliability management and community lending  we also help communities and families through grants and lowcost loans to our members that help support affordable housing and economic development initiatives fhlbi is one of  regional banks that make up the federal home loan bank system fhlbanks are governmentsponsored enterprises created by congress to ensure access to lowcost funding for their member financial institutions fhlbanks are privately capitalized and funded and receive no congressional appropriations the fhlbi is owned by its approximately  indiana and michigan financial institution members watch this  second video to learn more about how the fhlbanks support a nation of local lenders  explore the many ways we serve our members or contact us to learn more about our products and services and membership process member benefits as a cooperative we pass our borrowing benefits in the global debt markets on to our members in the form of lower borrowing costs which are subsequently passed on to consumers businesses and communities as an fhlbi member you are a shareholder and we strive to serve your needs learn more reliable liquidity fhlbi provides its members with safe consistent and reliable access to the capital market at a competitive price our borrowing power is backed by the collective strength of  federal home loan banks nationwide learn more mortgage purchasing fhlbis mortgage purchase program mpp provides members with a competitive secondary market outlet for highquality conforming fixedrate mortgages participating members can use this opportunity to reduce interest rate risk and create balance sheet flexibility learn more community  housing programs the fhlbi offers many programs to help finance local affordable housing and community development initiatives all funding is made available to our members who in turn pass it along to assist homebuyers homeowners housing finance authorities and community organizations learn more our membership at fhlbi our members are our owners our diverse base of bank thrift credit union insurance and community development financial institutions have access to products and services that help to promote the mission of supporting the housing market learn more resources in this section you will find forms relating to our affordable housing program our board of directors policies copies of our indepth member magazine forms and guides for our mortgage purchase program and much more learn more latest fhlbi news supporting homeless veterans at liberty village  affordable housing community housing news fhlbi member merchants bank of indiana helped bring a home to many homeless veterans in terre haute by providing funding to liberty village including a  affordable housing program grant second mentoring communities event raises the bar in frankfort indiana  affordable housing community investment news training fhlbis second mentoring communities event built on the success of the first one by giving attendees time to develop an action plan mentoring communities is a daylong gathering that brings in experts who have experienced development successes to serve as mentors view all news fhlbi  careers federal home loan bank of indianapolis careers explore the opportunities the federal home loan bank of indianapolis focuses on recruiting hiring developing and retaining a talented workforce by providing an environment that enables them to succeed diversity and inclusion are essential to building and maintaining our competitive edge—and are key to our current and future individual and business successes to provide bank staff with both personal and professional growth fhlbi offers excellent training and mentoring programs our current qualified staff includes more than  people with a wide range of abilities and backgrounds find your place on our team by exploring the following opportunities senior security engineer the federal home loan bank of indianapolis fhlbi has an exciting opportunity for a highly motivated individual to join our it team the senior security engineer will work closely with information technology teams and business partners to lead the design and implementation of security solutions to meet business objectives it initiatives and regulatory requirements you are responsible for ensuring the security infrastructure and all of its representative technologies are optimized adequately managed and monitored to protect the bank and its assets this position will be tasked with providing technical information security leadership and serve as a subject matter expert on information security technologies and best practices this role will work with it and business leaders to implement and manage a strong security posture and serve as technical escalation point for all security issues apply now security operations analyst the federal home loan bank of indianapolis fhlbi has an exciting opportunity for a highly motivated individual to join our security operations team the security operations analyst is responsible for managing the bank security infrastructure to ensure high levels of protection and availability to supported business applications this position will be responsible for assessing and analyzing threats identifying vulnerabilities and recommending appropriate actions to reduce security risks to the bank’s computer systems     apply now security operations analyst the federal home loan bank of indianapolis fhlbi has an exciting opportunity for a highly motivated individual to join our security operations team the security operations analyst is responsible for managing the bank security infrastructure to ensure high levels of protection and availability to supported business applications this position will be responsible for assessing and analyzing threats identifying vulnerabilities and recommending appropriate actions to reduce security risks to the bank’s computer systems     apply now senior database analyst the federal home loan bank of indianapolis fhlbi has an exciting opportunity for a highly motivated individual to join our data warehouse team the senior database analyst is responsible for assisting in configuring designing procuring installing maintaining and documenting database and network systems      apply now technical architect the federal home loan bank of indianapolis fhlbi has an exciting opportunity for a highly motivated individual to join our information technology team the technical architect is responsible for making recommendations about the banks organization of current systems components and how they relate to each other in their environments          apply now member research and strategies director the federal home loan bank of indianapolis has an exciting opportunity for a highly motivated individual to join our marketing team the member research and strategies director position is responsible for analyzing and interpreting economic and financial market data presenting to member institutions in webinars and at conferences modeling and analyzing balance sheets of financial institutions and developing assetliability product solutions and ideas develop strategy for bank use such as advances forecasts member segmentation whitepapers funding strategy tools for use by account managers and provide market updates provide solutions to members by using financial market data and balance sheet analysis to identify provide and educate members on bank products including the creation of whitepapers unique assetliability models procurement and relationship building with industry guest speakers and customized member balance sheet solutions             apply now working at fhlbi who we are diversity and inclusion fhlbi  communities  housing federal home loan bank of indianapolis communities  housing supporting community and housing initiatives when fhlbi opened its doors on oct   the mission was to restore housing finance and revitalize homeownership after thousands of families lost their homes during the great depression in  congress added the affordable housing program ahp as another tool for fhlbanks to use to help families afford housing today ahp is one of the most successful private sources of funding in the united states and has extended the fhlbanks’ original intent by furthering the idea that people deserve quality affordable homes fhlbi grants help members partner with community developers and public agencies to develop affordable housing in their communities fhlbi members have access to lowcost funding through our homeownership initiatives programs competitive ahp grants and community investment program cip which support all stages of housing and community economic development see the  annual report page of our affordable housing advisory council which advises the bank on low and moderateincome housing programs and housing needs in indiana and michigan homeownership initiatives​ in partnership with our members fhlbi offers three grant programs designed to address the homeownership needs of families throughout the life cycle of homeownership the homeownership opportunities program hop to help firsttime homebuyers with down payment assistance the neighborhood impact program nip to assist lowincome homeowners with home repairs and the accessibility modifications program amp  to aid seniors and households with disabled family members with home modifications that will allow them to remain in their current homes competitive affordable housing program each year fhlbi members partner with local notforprofit housing providers economic development  ​partners and housing developers to compete for affordable housing program ahp grants of up to  per project  these housing grants have changed lives and communities across indiana and michigan  since  the fhlbi has awarded over  million ​to create or rehabilitate single and multifamily affordable housing the competitive ahp funds ​projects ​involving the acquisition construction or rehabilitation of properties for families with annual incomes that are  or less than the area median income ami  learn more about the competitive affordable housing program   community investment program through its community investment program cip fhlbi provides members with atcost loans and letters of credit to support affordable housing and community economic development activities that benefit low and moderateincome families or neighborhoods these funds can be used to develop affordable housing for infrastructure improvements or to support local job creation through cip our members are making an incredible impact on their communities every day  learn more about cip advances community spirit awards each year fhlbi honors an individual from one indiana and one michigan member institution who shows an outstanding dedication to affordable housing and community economic development for more information about the awards and nomination criteria read  community spirit award page  community support ​review the community support regulation  cfr part  requires each member of fhlbi to submit a community support statement approximately once every two years each fhlbi member will receive a copy of the notice and the forms needed to comply with the requirement concurrently the bank will notify the fhlbi advisory council and nonprofit housing developers community groups and other interested parties in the district of the name of each member selected for review the community support statement form required by the federal housing finance agency is available to view   additional information relating to the form community support requirement and listing of current members selected for review are noted below community support statement instructions  css letter to interested parties current members selected for review federal register  community support final rule please visit the communities  housing section of the resources page bulletins presentations and publications for more general information about initiatives and announcements   affordable housing program ahp implementation plan community investment training homeownership opportunities program hop neighborhood impact program nip accessibility modification program amp community investment program competitive affordable housing program community spirit award resources fhlbi  products  services federal home loan bank of indianapolis products  services products  services fhlbi members have the ability to take advantage of a wide variety of products and services to assist with their liquidity interest rate risk management and operational needs  along with assisting with our members funding and liquidity needs our community investment and affordable housing programs allow our member to further economic and lowincome housing development in their communities who we are who we serve news credit services fhlbi credit products provide members a vital source of liquidity through access to advances loans lines of credit and letters of credit advances are offered in a full spectrum of terms with fixed floating amortizing or embedded option structures that can be tailored to meet our members funding and assetliability needs learn more mortgage purchase program fhlbi offers another funding tool the mortgage purchase program mpp which allows members to sell qualified  to year conforming fixedrate mortgages with ltvs up to  mpp offers a competitive rate as well as the potential for participating members to earn additional income if their loans perform well learn more correspondent services to meet their business operational needs fhlbi members rely on correspondent services such as automated clearinghouse ach net settlement securities safekeeping wire transfer and coin  currency learn more community investment program community investment program cip advances and letters of credit help members ensure that their communities experience steady economic growth learn more communities  housing programs for  years fhlbi has been offering affordable housing grants to our members who in turn partner with indiana and michigan communities to support low and verylow income families and neighborhoods each year our bank commits  of annual net income to fund affordable housing program ahp grants learn more fhlbi  contact us federal home loan bank of indianapolis contact us contact us do you know who youre looking for within fhlbi then click the department directory to the right for vendors looking to do business with the federal home loan bank of indianapolis please click the vendors button along the righthand side navigation for all other enquiries please reach us at federal home loan bank of indianapolis   woodfield crossing blvd  indianapolis indiana     toll free  to contact us by email fill out the fields below an fhlbi representative will respond to your email within one business day thank you for taking the time to contact us  please note use of contact form requires ie or above   please feel free to also use email memberservicesfhlbicom ​​if needed full name click to add john doe  institution click to add company name  telephone click to add   email click to add youremaildomaincom  subject click to add  message click to add  department directory vendors fhlbi  investor rel