about  bank credit union and insurance company members throughout indiana and michigan prior to becoming fhlbi president and ceo in  she had filled many diverse roles at the bank throughout her career including executive vice president cochief operating officer and chief financial officer fhlbi ranks th on the indianapolis business journal’s  list of “largest indianapolisarea private companies ms konich is also a board member of pentegra retirement services she holds a ba in economics from indiana university and earned her mba from iu’s kelley school of business in  the indianapolis business journal recognized her as a cfo of the year and in  the kelley school honored her with its academy of alumni fellows awardfhlbi has established itself as an expert in insurance industry lending best practices cindy and her team have also continued to grow the bank’s highly successful mortgage purchase program giving community lenders affordable reliable access to the secondary mortgage market  william miller executive vice president  chief risk officer  bill miller oversees fhlbis enterprisewide risk management function previously he was the banks chief capital markets officer overseeing all treasury and investments functions before joining fhlbi in  he served as the capital markets corporate expert for the federal deposit insurance corporation fdic in washington dc and from  served as senior vice president in financial markets at the federal home loan bank of chicago bill earned his undergraduate degree from the university of arizona and an mba from texas tech university  gregory teare executive vice president  chief financial officer  greg teare is responsible for credit services capital markets treasury balance sheet forecasting and fhlbis portfolio investments and hedging strategies additionally he oversees the funding assetliability management treasury risk analytics and strategic planning functions greg joined fhlbi in  as chief banking officer overseeing the mortgage purchase program and affordable housing and community investment programs gregs previous positions include risk management senior manager at pricewaterhousecoopers in seattle and vice president and director with the federal home loan bank of seattle he earned his undergraduate degree from ohio state university and an mba from the university of akron  chad brandt senior vice president  treasurer  chad oversees fhlbi’s capital markets activities including funding and debt issuance investments and market risk analysis chad also manages the onbalance sheet loan assets for the banks successful mortgage purchase program he joined fhlbi in january  as senior vptreasurer prior to joining fhlbi chad served as vice president of liquidity and funding for bmo harris bank in chicago chad also brings significant federal home loan bank experience to the bank having served as executive vice president of banking and advance products from  to  and in other finance roles at the federal home loan bank of chicago from  to  chad holds a bachelor’s degree in aerospace engineering from the university of virginia and an mba from duke university  jonathan griffin senior vice president  chief marketing officer  jon griffin is responsible for all marketing and sales functions to support fhlbis member products and services he also oversees the advance trading desk the membership recruitment and application process and member capital stock jon joined fhlbi in  as a senior credit operations analyst serving later as the advances manager then an account manager before being named first vpcredit services director in  where he oversaw all credit underwriting and collateral functions prior to joining fhlbi he spent three years in corporate finance with conseco jon holds a bachelors degree in finance from butler university and an mba with an emphasis in finance from indiana university’s kelley school of business he is a chartered financial analyst and a fellow of the life management institute   board of directors affordable housing advisory council who we are federal home loan bank of indianapolis private company information  bloomberg july    pm et banks company overview of federal home loan bank of indianapolis snapshot people company overview federal home loan bank of indianapolis operates as a regional wholesale bank in michigan and indiana the company operates through two segments traditional and mortgage loans the traditional segment offers various credit products including advances such as fixedrate bullet putable fixedrate amortizing adjustablerate variablerate and callable advances as well as customized advances letters of credit and lines of credit this segment also provides a portfolio of investments comprising federal funds sold securities purchased under agreement to resell afs securities and htm securities correspondent services consisting of wire transfer security safekeeping and settlement ser federal home loan bank of indianapolis operates as a regional wholesale bank in michigan and indiana the company operates through two segments traditional and mortgage loans the traditional segment offers various credit products including advances such as fixedrate bullet putable fixedrate amortizing adjustablerate variablerate and callable advances as well as customized advances letters of credit and lines of credit this segment also provides a portfolio of investments comprising federal funds sold securities purchased under agreement to resell afs securities and htm securities correspondent services consisting of wire transfer security safekeeping and settlement services to its member institutions and deposit products including overnight and demand deposits the mortgage loans segment purchases conforming medium or longterm fixedrate fully amortizing and level payment loans for primary owneroccupied and detached residences such as singlefamily properties and two three and fourunit properties this segment also purchases loans for primary owneroccupied and attached residences including condominiums and planned unit developments secondvacation homes and investment properties the company serves commercial banks savings associations credit unions community development financial institutions and insurance companies federal home loan bank of indianapolis was founded in  and is based in indianapolis indiana federal home loan bank of indianapolis is a subsidiary of federal home loan banks detailed description  woodfield crossing boulevardindianapolis in united statesfounded in  employees phone  wwwfhlbicom key executives for federal home loan bank of indianapolis ms cindy l konich chief executive officer and president age  mr gregory l teare chief financial officer and executive vice president age  mr deron j streitenberger chief business operations officer and senior vice president age  mr k lowell short jr chief accounting officer and senior vice president age  mr william d miller chief risk officer and executive vice president age  compensation as of fiscal year  federal home loan bank of indianapolis key developments federal home loan bank of indianapolis announces unaudited consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended march   apr   federal home loan bank of indianapolis announced unaudited consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended march   for the quarter the company reported net interest income after provision for credit losses was  million against  million a year ago as a result of asset growth and higher spreads net income was  million against  million a year ago primarily due to higher net interest income partially offset by net losses on derivatives and hedging activities federal home loan bank of indianapolis declares dividends payable april   apr   board of directors of the federal home loan bank of indianapolis declared dividends on class b and class b capital stock at annualized rates of  and  respectively the dividends will be paid in cash on april   federal home loan bank of indianapolis