 president and ceo the fhlbanks are regulated by the federal housing finance agency fhfa and are registered with the securities and exchange commission sec the council of fhlbanks is the trade association of the fhlbanks      read more  affordable housing  •••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• the fhlbanks affordable housing program ahp is the largest private source of grant funds for affordable housing in the united states it is funded with  percent of the fhlbanks net income each year     read more  cooperative structure  •••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• the fhlbanks are independent cooperatives privately capitalized and owned by thousands of financial institutions big and small from all  states us possessions and territories     read more  governance and regulation affordable housing cooperative structure everywhere in the us helping local lenders invest in jobs housing and economic growth in their communities visit fhlbank of san francisco arizona california nevada visit fhlbank of dallas arkansas louisiana mississippi new mexico texas visit fhlbank of topeka colorado kansas nebraska oklahoma visit fhlbank of des moines alaska guam hawaii idaho iowa minnesota missouri montana north dakota oregon south dakota utah washington wyoming visit fhlbank of chicago illinois wisconsin visit fhlbank of indianapolis indiana michigan visit fhlbank of atlanta alabama district of columbia florida georgia maryland north carolina south carolina virginia visit fhlbank of cincinnati kentucky ohio tennessee visit fhlbank of pittsburgh delaware pennsylvania west virginia visit fhlbank of new york new jersey new york puerto rico us virgin islands visit fhlbank of boston connecticut maine massachusetts new hampshire rhode island vermont want to know more ​   why do we need fhlbanks ​   how fhlbanks serve lenders ​   how liquidity builds communities ​   what makes it all work   the council of fhlbanks       l street nw suite  washington dc        or       fax    fhlbanks  all rights reserved fhlbi  home federal home loan bank of indianapolis about the federal home loan bank system  a nation of local lenders  watch the video fhlbi community and housing programs  learn more members are our shareholders  view investor relations careers  fhlbi  find your fit  shareholder symposium  discover new ways to transform your business  register now how we serve the federal home loan bank of indianapolis fhlbi is a regional wholesale bank that has been meeting the liquidity needs of member financial institutions throughout indiana and michigan since  our core mission is to provide a reliable source of liquidity to member banks credit unions community development financial institutions and insurance companies to support housing finance assetliability management and community lending  we also help communities and families through grants and lowcost loans to our members that help support affordable housing and economic development initiatives fhlbi is one of  regional banks that make up the federal home loan bank system fhlbanks are governmentsponsored enterprises created by congress to ensure access to lowcost funding for their member financial institutions fhlbanks are privately capitalized and funded and receive no congressional appropriations the fhlbi is owned by its approximately  indiana and michigan financial institution members watch this  second video to learn more about how the fhlbanks support a nation of local lenders  explore the many ways we serve our members or contact us to learn more about our products and services and membership process member benefits as a cooperative we pass our borrowing benefits in the global debt markets on to our members in the form of lower borrowing costs which are subsequently passed on to consumers businesses and communities as an fhlbi member you are a shareholder and we strive to serve your needs learn more reliable liquidity fhlbi provides its members with safe consistent and reliable access to the capital market at a competitive price our borrowing power is backed by the collective strength of  federal home loan banks nationwide learn more mortgage purchasing fhlbis mortgage purchase program mpp provides members with a competitive secondary market outlet for highquality conforming fixedrate mortgages participating members can use this opportunity to reduce interest rate risk and create balance sheet flexibility learn more community  housing programs the fhlbi offers many programs to help finance local affordable housing and community development initiatives all funding is made available to our members who in turn pass it along to assist homebuyers homeowners housing finance authorities and community organizations learn more our membership at fhlbi our members are our owners our diverse base of bank thrift credit union insurance and community development financial institutions have access to products and services that help to promote the mission of supporting the housing market learn more resources in this section you will find forms relating to our affordable housing program our board of directors policies copies of our indepth member magazine forms and guides for our mortgage purchase program and much more learn more latest fhlbi news supporting homeless veterans at liberty village  affordable housing community housing news fhlbi member merchants bank of indiana helped bring a home to many homeless veterans in terre haute by providing funding to liberty village including a  affordable housing program grant second mentoring communities event raises the bar in frankfort indiana  affordable housing community investment news training fhlbis second mentoring communities event built on the success of the first one by giving attendees time to develop an action plan mentoring communities is a daylong gathering that brings in expe